other_tests.findings: Focal increase in intra-epithelial lymphocytes, with villous shortening, edema, irregularity, and vacuolation of the surface epithelium suggesting an enteropathy.
Leptin levels were appropriate for the degree of obesity (35 ng/ml), excluding congenital leptin deficiency.

other_tests.procedure_name: Fasting plasma insulin and proinsulin measurements
other_tests.findings: Proinsulin was markedly elevated (1079 pmol/liter), while insulin levels were inappropriately low (14 pmol/liter).
Basal metabolic rate measured by indirect calorimetry was normal for age and gender-specific equations (7.3 MJ/d).
Markedly elevated at 549 pmol/liter, indicating impaired POMC processing.
Elevated TSH (4.8 pmol/liter) with free T4 concentration at the lower end of the normal range (10.2 pmol/liter), suggestive of hypothalamic hypothyroidism.
